---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/tools';

const lastUpdated = 'May 23, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Workspace Lux"
  description="Terms of service for Workspace Lux. Our calculators provide estimates only and do not constitute professional lighting or engineering advice."
  path="/terms"
>
  <article class="max-w-site mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 prose-content">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-main mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p>
      By accessing or using Workspace Lux at {SITE.url}, you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do
      not agree, please do not use the site.
    </p>

    <h2>About the service</h2>
    <p>
      Workspace Lux provides free online lighting calculators, guides, and educational content for
      offices, desks, and related workspaces. The site is offered “as is” for general information and
      planning purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Not professional advice</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>
        Calculator results and guide content are simplified estimates only. They do not constitute
        professional lighting design, electrical engineering, architectural, legal, or compliance advice.
      </strong>
      Actual lighting performance depends on fixture photometrics, mounting height, room geometry,
      reflectance, controls, daylight, glare, local building codes, and occupational standards. You are
      responsible for verifying requirements with qualified professionals and applicable authorities
      before specifying, installing, or relying on any lighting system.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy and limitations</h2>
    <p>
      We strive for accurate formulas and helpful explanations, but we do not warrant that outputs are
      complete, error-free, or suitable for any particular project. Presets and defaults are generalized
      — your situation may differ. We may change calculators, content, or availability at any time
      without notice.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the site in any unlawful manner or to harm others</li>
      <li>Attempt to disrupt, scrape, or overload our systems</li>
      <li>Misrepresent affiliation with Workspace Lux</li>
      <li>Reproduce substantial portions of the site for commercial redistribution without permission</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      Site content, branding, and original materials are owned by Workspace Lux or used with permission.
      You may link to our pages and use calculators for personal or internal business planning. Other
      uses require our prior written consent unless permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party links and advertising</h2>
    <p>
      The site may include links to third-party websites or display advertising. We are not responsible
      for third-party content, products, or privacy practices. Any transactions with third parties are
      solely between you and them.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, Workspace Lux disclaims all warranties, express or implied,
      including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. Your use of the
      site is at your sole risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, Workspace Lux and its operators shall not be liable for any
      indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits, data,
      or business opportunities arising from your use of the site or reliance on calculator results —
      even if advised of the possibility of such damages.
    </p>

    <h2>Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Workspace Lux from claims arising out of your misuse of the
      site or violation of these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by applicable laws in the jurisdiction where Workspace Lux operates,
      without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Disputes shall be resolved in the competent courts of
      that jurisdiction, unless mandatory consumer protection laws in your country provide otherwise.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use after the updated date constitutes
      acceptance of the revised Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
